Direct thermometry of the pancreas in the postoperative period. Direct thermometry of the pancreas in 44 patients after operations for carcinoma of the pancreato-duodenal zone or chronic pancreatitis has shown a relationship between temperature of the pancreas stump and the fermentemia degree. Characteristic changes of temperature regimens are observed 5-17 hours earlier than manifestations of clinical symptoms of postoperative pancreatitis make their appearance.